message.content:
cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on energy consumption of multi-core embedded programs and a specific embedded processor architecture, XS1.
- cs.AR (Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses improvements and extensions to a previous energy model for the XS1 architecture.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper presents a software development process workflow for estimating energy consumption and integrates the energy model into a larger scale model of a network of interconnected cores.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper evaluates the accuracy of the models using benchmarks and discusses how results can be presented and interpreted.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as the paper focuses on integrating energy consumption estimation into a software developer's workflow.
